The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump declaring October 8, 2018, as Columbus Day in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the achievements of Christopher Columbus, an Italian explorer who discovered the Americas in 1492. It highlights Columbus's courage, determination, and ambition, which have inspired generations of Americans. The proclamation also acknowledges the contributions of Italian Americans to the country's culture, business, and civic life. The Congress has previously requested the President to proclaim the second Monday of October each year as Columbus Day. The proclamation encourages the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and for the flag of the United States to be displayed on all public buildings in honor of the nation's diverse history and contributors.